# Docs MDX — end-user voice

Audience: developers **using** `@polyms/core-ui` in their app. Not maintainers, not monorepo contributors.

Also follow [docs-mdx-heading-style.mdc](docs-mdx-heading-style.mdc) (no inline code in headings).

## Voice

Write **what to do** and **why it helps the product UI** — not how the library is built.

| Avoid (maintainer) | Prefer (end user) |
| --- | --- |
| `core/src/styles/_*.css`, monorepo paths | "Import `@polyms/core-ui` styles" |
| Base UI / `@base-ui/react` / re-export internals | Component API and usage |
| "bundled classes", `_accordion.css`, build pipeline | "Import package styles so motion applies" |
| "design-system", "Core-UI shorthand", "Polyms defaults" | Plain product language |
| Skill file maps, routing tables, agent skill internals | Install steps + links to Design System |
| "consumers should", "this repo", "we ship" | "you", "your app", "the library" |

**OK to keep:** `CSS-only` (no React export), WAI-ARIA pattern links, peer deps (`zustand`), `import from '@polyms/core-ui'`, API Reference frontmatter.

## Tables

GFM markdown tables (`| col | col |`) **do not render** in this MDX setup — they appear as one broken line.

Use a JSX table (see `agent-skill.mdx`, `field.mdx`, `design-system.mdx`):

```mdx
export const rows = [
  { a: 'Situation', b: 'What to do' },
]

<div className='card my-4'>
  ...
</div>
```

## TSX code fences (Prettier)

Prettier inserts a leading `;` before JSX when `<Component` starts a line after `import` (ASI guard). Wrap snippets in a **`const` with a meaningful name** — not `example`.

Name from the root JSX tag: `Field` → `field`, `Field.Floating` → `fieldFloating`, `Modal.Content` → `modalContent`, `<a>` → `link`, `<table>` → `table`.

```tsx
import { Field } from '@polyms/core-ui'

const emailField = (
  <Field required>
    <Field.Label>Email</Field.Label>
    <Field.Control />
  </Field>
)
```

Single-line: `const saveButton = <Button variant='primary'>Save</Button>`. Multiple sibling roots: `const shortcuts = (<>…</>)` or separate `const` per snippet (`const smallModal = …`). Helper: `node docs/scripts/wrap-mdx-jsx-examples.mjs`.

## Page shape

1. **Intro** — one short paragraph: what it is + when to use it.
2. **CodePreview** demo (if component page).
3. **Usage** — copy-paste examples from `@polyms/core-ui`.
4. **Notes** (optional) — pitfalls for app authors, not file paths.
5. **API Reference** — `<APIReference />` when frontmatter `apis` is set.

## `-views/`

Demo components under `docs/src/pages/docs/-views/` are site internals. Do not document `-views/` paths or plugin wiring in prose meant for package users.
